Class ValueList

java.lang.Object
  engine.ValueList
public class ValueList
extends java.lang.Object

A two-dimensional array with methods relating to sorting and selecting values. ValueLists are created by parsing .csv files for stimuli lists. After grabbing the values, the values are ordered, and can be selected one at a time from the TestingEngine to be displayed by the Gui.

Constructor Detail

ValueList

public ValueList(java.io.File file)
Creates a new ValueList. The file (Excel .csv) passed must comply with the stimulus list standards, to wit: Line 1 must be the stimulus type, e.g. one_word_two_picts; line 2 must be the insructions, formatted in HTML; if there are examples, line 3 must state "", after which examples are given as normal stimuli. Following each example, the next line must contain the feedback for a correct response, the line after must contain the feedback for and incorrect response. The block is terminated by the line "". The remaining lines must be columns of values for the stimulus and choices. Note that blank lines are ignored.

Parameters:
file - The .csv file to be parsed
